The product of a matrix and its inverse is the identity matrix, so we have
\[\begin{pmatrix} 2 & a \\ -3 & -1 \end{pmatrix}
\begin{pmatrix} -\frac{1}{16} & b \\ \frac{3}{16} & \frac{1}{8} \end{pmatrix}
=
\begin{pmatrix} 1 & 0 \\ 0 & 1 \end{pmatrix}.\]This gives us $\frac{-1}{8} + \frac{3a}{16} = 1$ and $2b - a = 0.$  Solving, we find $(a,b) = \boxed{(8,4)}.$
